            <thetext>Currently the &quot;get&quot; and &quot;render&quot; methods of the &quot;template&quot; module offer similar functionality. The first does return a DOM structure (collection) and the latter returns the rendered string.

The &quot;get&quot; method does use a ID of the root element of the template (stored in the DOM) and the &quot;render&quot; method does use a template as string as input value.

It would be great to have a third method which uses a template as a string as input value and returns a collection. So the developer doesn&#39;t have to create a template stored in the DOM to get a rendered template as a collection.</thetext>
